FBIS4-58944 "drnes090_c_94009" FBIS-NES-94-090 Daily Report 7 May 1994 Egypt Fifteen Extremists `Repent,' Surrender in Asyut Fifteen Extremists `Repent,' Surrender in Asyut NC0705125394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1210 GMT 7 May 94 NC0705125394 Cairo MENA Arabic BFN [Text] Asyut, Upper Egypt, 7 May (MENA)--Governor of Asyut Samih al-Sa'id stated that 15 members of extremist groups gave themselves up today, declaring their repentance and their return to the right course. He said these repenters turned themselves over through the National Democratic Party's popular and political apparatuses.
